                            <comment id="12994399" author="streamy" created="Mon, 14 Feb 2011 18:09:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In some of the HLog improvements that Dhruba and I have been working on, we&apos;ve become dependent on the LogSyncer thread.  However, this is also still using an HBase-side group commit.  Just an FYI (alternative implementations of HLog might be a neat idea, there are lots of different ways to optimize depending on the use case)... don&apos;t let it hold you up.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expect some patches this week around this stuff.  Currently tracking down a pesky race condition.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12994471" author="larsgeorge" created="Mon, 14 Feb 2011 20:21:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We better wait then and see what you&apos;ve got. Love the improvements done recently in this area.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13047672" author="stack" created="Fri, 10 Jun 2011 22:58:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving out of 0.92.  Move it back in if you think differently.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13047687" author="stack" created="Fri, 10 Jun 2011 22:58:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving out of 0.92.  Move it back in if you think differently.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13882462" author="stack" created="Sun, 26 Jan 2014 22:38:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No LogSyncer thread anymore.  The log writing has been refactored.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
